menu "FaceGuard Compatibility"

config TIE728_BOOST
    bool "Force TIE728 path in ESP-DL (IDF v6.0 fix)"
    default y if IDF_TARGET_ESP32S3
    help
        CONFIG_TIE728_BOOST was removed from IDF v6.0 Kconfig but ESP-DL 3.2.4
        still references it via #if CONFIG_TIE728_BOOST in dl_tool_cache.cpp.
        Enabling this forces the correct TIE728 vector instruction path on
        ESP32-S3 and avoids a compile error caused by an outdated struct
        initialiser in the fallback #else branch.

endmenu
